🎓 Ready to explore what UofT has to offer? Join us this Saturday, August 17th, at 3:00 PM for a virtual seminar where you can learn all about the amazing clubs at UofT, including iGEM Toronto! 🌟

Discover how you can get involved in student-led initiatives, learn about our projects in synthetic biology, and hear from other incredible clubs like Step UofT and Global Brigades. This is your chance to find your community and make the most of your university experience! 📚👥

📅 Date: Saturday, August 17
🕒 Time: 3:00 PM
📍 Location: Virtual

Register now and take the first step in finding your perfect club!
👉 Event Registration: 
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdDgQD5FObUDyHGDvWu_2JHfLzuSAmyVbbomK2qahmSkr7ncw/viewform 

See you there! 💻

#UofT #StudentLife #iGEMToronto #UofTClubs #UniversityClubs #GetInvolved #Mentorship #GlobalBrigades

🧬🗣️ Ready to dive into the exciting intersection of AI and biotechnology? Join us for the iGEM Toronto x Hart House Debate Club event on August 27th at 6 pm! We’ll be debating the future of generative AI in tackling antibiotic resistance—a critical issue in modern medicine.

Whether you’re passionate about science, ethics, or just love a good debate, this event is for you! You can sign up as a debater, audience member, or even a guest speaker. Plus, enjoy some free pizza and drinks while engaging in thought-provoking discussions! 🍕💬

🔗 Sign up now: https://forms.gle/x5zqugEciW7YVnsN7

Don't miss out on this chance to make your voice heard on one of the most pressing issues in science today. See you there! #iGEM #AI #AntibioticResistance #Debate #TorontoEvents #harthousedebate

Catch us at the UTSU Club Fair on August 30 (booth E47), 1pm to 4pm at Devonshire Place next to Varsity Field! Have a chance to find out more about our work and Associate recruitment for the coming school year, as well as pick up some stickers! Check out our story highlights for a map of the area and where to find us. See you there!

Are you passionate about sustainable development, volunteering abroad and empowering communities to achieve a higher standard of well-being? Are you looking to build skills and gain experiences you can leverage in your future career? Then apply to be a U of T Global Brigades executive.

UTGB partners with local communities in Central America to implement holistic and sustainable development programs that aim to resolve health and economic disparities.

We are now accepting applications for multiple executive positions. As a member of the executive team, you will meet like-minded individuals who are passionate and work together to achieve the mission of Global Brigades. You will also build an invaluable set of transferable skills and gain experiences you can discuss at length in a future interview!

Details about the roles and responsibilities of each position are linked at the beginning of the application from.

(LINK IN BIO) Application form UTGB24-25 Rolling Basis

Learn more about Global Brigades here https://www.globalbrigades.org/
